<header>
<div id="instruction">
	Choose the pieces of advice that you think you should follow in answering IELTS Writing Task 1.
</div>
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/SS_GW_007.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  
<div id="targetspotting">
  <p><g id="t1">A.  Brainstorm for ideas first.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t2">B.  Close the letter appropriately.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t3">C.  Copy the writing task and use it as your opening sentence.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t4">D.  Cover all the points in the writing task.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t5">E.  Decide if you have to write a formal or informal letter.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t6">F.  Decide what the purpose of the letter is.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t7">G.  Divide your letter into paragraphs.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t8">H.  Follow the instructions.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t9">I.  Include all the ideas you brainstormed.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t10">J.  Include irrelevant information.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t11">K.  Leave out any of the points mentioned in the task.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t12">L.  Leave some time at the end to check your letter for mistakes.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t13">M.  Make a quick plan for your letter.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t14">N.  Open the letter appropriately.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t15">O.  Read the writing task carefully.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t16">P.  Spend more than 20 minutes on Writing Task 1.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t17">Q.  Start writing your letter immediately.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t18">R.  Think about who you have to write to.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t19">S.  Write a prepared answer.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t20">T.  Write fewer than 150 words.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t21">U.  Write one paragraph.</g></p>
  <p><g id="t22">V.  Write your address.</g></p>
</div>
</section>

